</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="385" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[828,1463,216,1175]" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis box="[858,1088,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Description of female</emphasis>
: Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[1244,1325,461,483]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[125,156,1514,1533]" captionTargetBox="[138,1457,160,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[125,1463,151,1508]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1: A Persiscape caspica sp. n., ♀ habitus; B same, ♂ habitus; C Persilena sengleti sp. n., ♀ habitus; D Asiascape parthica sp. n., ♂ habitus; E Gorbiscape gorbachevi sp. n., ♂ habitus; F same, ♀ habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3925219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3925219/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
. Total length 10.04. Carapace 3.76 long, 2.30 wide. Eye sizes and PME interdistance: AME: 0.18, ALE: 0.20, PME: 0.20, PLE: 0.21, PME–PME: 0.10. Chelicera with 2 prolateral and 3 retrolateral teeth. Carapace, sternum, labium, chelicera, and maxilla light brown. Carapace with dark margins, two wide, light submarginal bands, two wide, brown lateral bands, and a wide, light median band. Legs the same colour as the carapace and lacking distinct annulations. Abdomen light gray with scattered darker patches dorsally and with two longitudinal dark gray bands ventrally. Spinnerets uniformly light yellowish. Leg I measurements: 11.47 (2.94, 1.29, 2.52, 2.64, 2.08).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[828,1463,216,1175]" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">
Epigyne as in 
<figureCitation box="[1023,1111,911,933]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[125,156,1431,1450]" captionTargetBox="[126,1461,151,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[126,1461,151,1406]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 14: Epigynes. A Gorbiscape gorbachevi sp. n., intact, ventral view; B same, macerated, dorsal view; C, D same, posterior views; E, F Asiascape parthica sp. n., intact, ventral views; G same, macerated, dorsal view; H same, posterior view; I Persilena sengleti sp. n., posterior view; D same, intact, ventral view; K same, antero-ventral view; L same, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: Cd = copulatory duct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3925245" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3925245/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Figs. 14</figureCitation>
I–L, plate slightly extends over epigastric furrow, suboval, rebordered anteriorly; fovea absent, copulatory openings slit-like, indistinct; endogyne almost as long as wide and as deep as wide, with the copulatory ducts extended dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[828,1463,216,1175]" box="[858,1039,1082,1106]" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis box="[858,913,1082,1106]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Male</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
